                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12938055" author="robertburrelldonkin" created="Wed, 14 Jun 2006 04:31:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Uber jar licensing seems like a thorny issue to me and probably one that&apos;s quite a bit bigger than just ActiveMQ. Once I find some time, I should raise this on legal, write up some documentation in the release and then talk to the maveneers. If I don&apos;t before you&apos;re next release, please feel free to kick me (gently).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12938141" author="chirino" created="Thu, 15 Jun 2006 21:14:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve changed the build so that NOTICE and LICENSE files do not overwrite one another anymore.  Those files are moved&lt;br/&gt;
the the META-INF/${jar-name/ directory before we extract the next jar into the uber jar.  So it&apos;s now possible to look at the original LICENSE, DISCLAIMER,NOTICE, and COPYRIGHT files that were include in each jar of the uber jar.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please let me know if that&apos;s still does not meet the requirements.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12937821" author="chirino" created="Thu, 15 Jun 2006 21:21:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I updated the project name to apache-incubator-activemq so that distributions include the apache in it.  Fixing the issues with the META-INF and the having the src distro extract to directory with -src on it, I think will involve getting some help from the maven team.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12937794" author="chirino" created="Thu, 15 Jun 2006 21:28:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied changes to 4.1 and partially to 4.0... I think changing the module name on a big fix release would be in bad form.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
